## Examples of null Contracts in Employment Law

In employment settings, null contracts often arise from discriminatory clauses or violation of labor statutes. Consider a job agreement that includes unpaid overtime demands conflicting with minimum wage laws—it becomes null in regions recognizing employee protections. Similarly, contracts omitting termination conditions or dispute resolution mechanisms may face nullity challenges.

Notable null contract scenarios:
- Non-compete clauses restricting legitimate career moves
- Waivers denying statutory benefits like family leave
- Agreements based on misrepresented company policies

